The fair value of our short-term borrowings reflects current market interest rates and approximates the amounts we
have recorded on our consolidated balance sheets. The fair value of our term loans was determined using quoted
prices for similar instruments in markets that are not active (Level 2 valuation data) and approximates the amounts we
have recorded on our consolidated balance sheets. The fair value of our long-term debt was determined using quoted
prices in active markets (Level 1 valuation data) for the publicly traded debt obligations.
